{"transcription":"Speaker 1 (Dallin H. Oaks): My dear brothers and sisters, we meet as we mourn the death of our beloved President Russell M. Nelson. I speak to you as the President of the Quorum of the Twelve, a position in which I have been sustained in our ward, stake, and general conferences for the past seven and a half years. We will go forward with this semi-annual general conference, proceeding as planned with speakers and music assigned by President Nelson after months of preparation. The only additions are my introductory explanation and my speaking in place of President Nelson in the closing session on Sunday afternoon.\n\nThis is the first time in about 75 years that a church president has died a few days before general conference. That required planning to hold the vital leadership meetings connected with general conference and this general session while scheduling his funeral as soon as possible. President Nelson understood the value of general conference to provide direction to the saints in the coming months. We honor him by following the planned conference schedule he approved.\n\nIn this time of grief we have already held a meeting to pay tribute to President Russell M. Nelson before our general conference meetings and then scheduled his funeral as soon as possible after conference. All of this has been done with the approval of President Nelson’s family and the Quorum of the Twelve.\n\nSince all of us assigned to speak in general conference would like to devote our time to paying personal tribute to President Nelson, we have asked that all conference speakers keep such tributes to a minimum, deferring elaborate tributes to the funeral, which we have begun to plan.\n\nMy own brief tribute, suitable to this conference and to the tributes we have already paid, is this: I love Russell M. Nelson, and I have learned more about the gospel and gospel leadership from my long friendship and association with him than from any other leader I have personally known. He is our model as a servant and follower of the Lord Jesus Christ. Of these things I testify in the name of Jesus Christ, amen.","summary":["Dallin H. Oaks announced the death of President Russell M. Nelson and identified himself as President of the Quorum of the Twelve.","The semi-annual general conference will proceed as planned with speakers and music assigned by President Nelson, with Oaks adding an introductory explanation and replacing Nelson in the Sunday closing session.","This is the first time in about 75 years that a church president has died a few days before general conference, which required coordinating vital leadership meetings and scheduling his funeral while preserving conference ceremonies.","Plans for tributes and the funeral were made with the approval of President Nelson’s family and the Quorum of the Twelve.","Conference speakers were asked to keep personal tributes brief and to defer more elaborate tributes to the funeral.","Oaks offered a brief personal tribute expressing his love for President Nelson and testifying that he learned more about gospel leadership from him than from any other leader."]}
